0after%20a%20diplomatic%20dispute%20that%20lead%20to%20China%20imposing%20a%20raft%20of%20restrictions%20on%20Australian%20agricultural%20and%20mineral%20exports%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENative%20to%20China%2C%20pandas%20have%20through%20the%20years%20become%20%26quot%3Benvoys%20of%20friendship%26quot%3B%2C%20earning%20China's%20outreach%20to%20countries%20it%20gifts%20the%20animals%20to%20the%20name%20of%20panda%20diplomacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20also%20been%20used%20to%20show%20Chinese%20anger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20is%20panda%20diplomacy%20and%20how%20does%20it%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHEN%20DID%20PANDA%20DIPLOMACY%20START%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20founding%20in%201949%2C%20the%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China%20has%20used%20panda%20diplomacy%20to%20boost%20its%20international%20image%20by%20gifting%20or%20lending%20panda%20to%20foreign%20zoos%20as%20goodwill%20animal%20ambassadors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Chinese%20leader%20Mao%20Zedong%20in%201957%20gifted%20a%20panda%2C%20Ping%20Ping%2C%20to%20the%20former%20Soviet%20Union%20to%20celebrate%20the%2040th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20October%20Revolution%20that%20ushered%20in%20the%20Soviet%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20further%20cement%20ties%20with%20its%20socialist%20allies%2C%20China%20dispatched%20another%20panda%20to%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%201959%20and%20five%20more%20to%20North%20Korea%20between%201965%20and%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201972%2C%20Beijing%20gifted%20two%20pandas%2C%20Ling%20Ling%20and%20Hsing%20Hsing%2C%20to%20the%20United%20States%20after%20then%20President%20Richard%20Nixon's%20historic%20visit%2C%20in%20a%20sign%20of%20normalised%20China-U.S.%20relations%20and%20marking%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20for%20China's%20foreign%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20other%20countries%20including%20Japan%2C%20France%2C%20Britain%20and%20Spain%20have%20also%20been%20given%20panda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHAT'S%20THE%20PANDA%20DIPLOMACY%20POLICY%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%201984%2C%20China%20stopped%20gifting%20pandas%20due%20to%20their%20dwindling%20numbers%20and%20began%20loaning%20them%20to%20overseas%20zoos%20instead%2C%20often%20in%20pairs%20for%2010%20years%2C%20with%20an%20annual%20fee%20of%20up%20to%20about%20%241%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20keeping%20pandas%20can%20be%20costly%20for%20zoos%2C%20they%20are%20seen%20as%20drawcards%20for%20visitors%20and%20help%20generate%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pandas%20typically%20return%20home%20to%20southwest%20China%20after%20the%20loan%20agreement%20ends.%20Panda%20cubs%20born%20overseas%20are%20no%20exception%2C%20and%20would%20be%20sent%20home%20between%20the%20age%20of%20two%20and%20four%20to%20join%20a%20Chinese%20breeding%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHOW%20DOES%20IT%20WORK%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20a%20history%20of%20using%20pandas%20to%20reward%20its%20trading%20partners.%20A%202013%20Oxford%20University%20study%20said%20the%20timing%20of%20China's%20lease%20of%20pandas%20to%20Canada%2C%20France%20and%20Australia%20%26quot%3Bcoincided%20with%26quot%3B%20uranium%20deals%20and%20contracts%20with%20these%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panda%20agreements%20with%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20Singapore%2C%20Malaysia%20and%20Thailand%2C%20also%20coincided%20with%20the%20signing%20of%20free-trade%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20pandas%20are%20also%20used%20to%20express%20China's%20displeasure%20with%20a%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20China%20recalled%20two%20U.S.-born%20pandas%2C%20Tai%20Shan%20and%20Mei%20Lan%2C%20after%20Beijing%20warned%20Washington%20against%20a%20scheduled%20meeting%20between%20then-President%20Barack%20Obama%20and%20the%20Dalai%20Lama%2C%20which%20Beijing%20views%20as%20a%20dangerous%20separatist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20downturn%20in%20bilateral%20ties%2C%20Ya%20Ya%2C%20on%20loan%20to%20the%20U.S.%20for%2020%20years%2C%20was%20returned%20in%20April%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConcerns%20over%20her%20health%20had%20also%20fanned%20nationalist%20sentiment%20on%20China's%20social%20media%2C%20with%20animal%20advocates%20accusing%20the%20Memphis%20Zoo%20in%20Tennessee%20of%20providing%20inadequate%20care%20to%20the%20animal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%20last%20year%2C%20three%20other%20pandas%20left%2C%20leaving%20only%20four%20giant%20pandas%20on%20U.S.%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20month%2C%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20then%20hinted%20that%20he%20was%20open%20to%20sending%20more%20pandas%20to%20the%20U.S.%20after%20meeting%20with%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20in%20California%2C%20a%20gesture%20seen%20as%20Chinese%20willingness%20to%20improve%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EARE%20PANDAS%20STILL%20ENDANGERED%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20domestic%20conservation%20programmes%20have%20seen%20the%20status%20of%20pandas%20improve%20from%20endangered%20to%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20population%20of%20giant%20pandas%20in%20the%20wild%20has%20grown%20from%20around%201%2C100%20in%20the%201980s%20to%201%2C900%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20currently%20728%20pandas%20in%20zoos%20and%20breeding%20centres%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718767320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fsi0s8sk8_panda-afp-_625x300_16_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-is-chinas-panda-diplomacy-how-it-works-5920814%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22During%20a%20visit%20to%20Australia%20this%20week%2C%20Chinese%20Premier%20Li%20Qiang%20made%20a%20classic%20goodwill%20gesture%20that%20boded%20well%20for%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20countries%3A%20he%20offered%20to%20send%20pandas.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-is-chinas-panda-diplomacy-how-it-works-5920814%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-is-chinas-panda-diplomacy-how-it-works-5920814%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-is-chinas-panda-diplomacy-how-it-works-5920814%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20Than%20550%20Hajj%20Pilgrims%20Die%20In%20Mecca%20In%20Blazing%20Heat%20Nearing%2052%20Degrees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDiplomats%20on%20Tuesday%20said%20at%20least%20550%20pilgrims%20died%20during%20the%20hajj%2C%20underscoring%20the%20gruelling%20nature%20of%20the%20pilgrimage%20which%20again%20unfolded%20in%20scorching%20temperatures%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20323%20of%20those%20who%20died%20were%20Egyptians%2C%20most%20of%20them%20succumbing%20to%20heat-related%20illnesses%2C%20two%20Arab%20diplomats%20coordinating%20their%20countries'%20responses%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20them%20(the%20Egyptians)%20died%20because%20of%20heat%26quot%3B%20except%20for%20one%20who%20sustained%20fatal%20injuries%20during%20a%20minor%20crowd%20crush%2C%20one%20of%20the%20diplomats%20said%2C%20adding%20the%20total%20figure%20came%20from%20the%20hospital%20morgue%20in%20the%20Al-Muaisem%20neighbourhood%20of%20Mecca.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2060%20Jordanians%20also%20died%2C%20the%20diplomats%20said%2C%20up%20from%20an%20official%20tally%20of%2041%20given%20earlier%20on%20Tuesday%20by%20Amman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20deaths%20bring%20the%20total%20reported%20so%20far%20by%20multiple%20countries%20to%20577%2C%20according%20to%20an%20AFP%20tally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20diplomats%20said%20the%20total%20at%20the%20morgue%20in%20Al-Muaisem%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20in%20Mecca%2C%20was%20550.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hajj%20is%20one%20of%20the%20five%20pillars%20of%20Islam%20and%20all%20Muslims%20with%20the%20means%20must%20complete%20it%20at%20least%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pilgrimage%20is%20increasingly%20affected%20by%20climate%20change%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Saudi%20study%20published%20last%20month%20that%20said%20temperatures%20in%20the%20area%20where%20rituals%20are%20performed%20were%20rising%200.4%20degrees%20Celsius%20(0.72%20degrees%20Fahrenheit)%20each%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETemperatures%20hit%2051.8%20degrees%20Celsius%20(125%20Fahrenheit)%20at%20the%20Grand%20Mosque%20in%20Mecca%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20Saudi%20national%20meteorology%20centre%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeat%20stress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Egypt's%20foreign%20ministry%20said%20Cairo%20was%20collaborating%20with%20Saudi%20authorities%20on%20search%20operations%20for%20Egyptians%20who%20had%20gone%20missing%20during%20the%20hajj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20ministry%20statement%20said%20%26quot%3Ba%20certain%20number%20of%20deaths%26quot%3B%20had%20occurred%2C%20it%20did%20not%20specify%20whether%20Egyptians%20were%20among%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaudi%20authorities%20have%20reported%20treating%20more%20than%202%2C000%20pilgrims%20suffering%20from%20heat%20stress%20but%20have%20not%20updated%20that%20figure%20since%20Sunday%20and%20have%20not%20provided%20information%20on%20fatalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20240%20pilgrims%20were%20reported%20dead%20by%20various%20countries%20last%20year%2C%20most%20of%20them%20Indonesians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAFP%20journalists%20in%20Mina%2C%20outside%20Mecca%2C%20on%20Monday%20saw%20pilgrims%20pouring%20bottles%20of%20water%20over%20their%20heads%20as%20volunteers%20handed%20out%20cold%20drinks%20and%20fast-melting%20chocolate%20ice%20cream%20to%20help%20them%20keep%20cool.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaudi%20officials%20had%20advised%20pilgrims%20to%20use%20umbrellas%2C%20drink%20plenty%20of%20water%20and%20avoid%20exposure%20to%20the%20sun%20during%20the%20hottest%20hours%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20of%20the%20hajj%20rituals%2C%20including%20the%20prayers%20on%20Mount%20Arafat%20which%20took%20place%20on%20Saturday%2C%20involve%20being%20outdoors%20for%20hours%20in%20the%20daytime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20pilgrims%20described%20seeing%20motionless%20bodies%20on%20the%20roadside%20and%20ambulance%20services%20that%20appeared%20overwhelmed%20at%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%201.8%20million%20pilgrims%20took%20part%20in%20the%20hajj%20this%20year%2C%201.6%20million%20of%20them%20from%20abroad%2C%20according%20to%20Saudi%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnregistered%20pilgrims%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20year%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20pilgrims%20attempt%20to%20perform%20the%20hajj%20through%20irregular%20channels%20as%20they%20cannot%20afford%20the%20often%20costly%20procedures%20for%20official%20hajj%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20places%20these%20off-the-books%20pilgrims%20at%20risk%20as%20they%20cannot%20access%20air-conditioned%20facilities%20provided%20by%20Saudi%20authorities%20along%20the%20hajj%20route.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20diplomats%20who%20spoke%20to%20AFP%20on%20Tuesday%20said%20that%20the%20Egyptian%20death%20toll%20was%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%26quot%3B%20boosted%20by%20a%20large%20number%20of%20unregistered%20Egyptian%20pilgrims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIrregular%20pilgrims%20caused%20great%20chaos%20in%20the%20Egyptian%20pilgrims'%20camps%2C%20causing%20the%20collapse%20of%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20an%20Egyptian%20official%20supervising%20the%20country's%20hajj%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pilgrims%20went%20without%20food%2C%20water%2C%20or%20air%20conditioning%20for%20a%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20died%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20the%20heat%20because%20most%20people%20had%20no%20place%26quot%3B%20to%20take%20shelter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20Saudi%20officials%20said%20they%20had%20cleared%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20unregistered%20pilgrims%20from%20Mecca%20ahead%20of%20the%20hajj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20countries%20to%20report%20deaths%20during%20the%20hajj%20this%20year%20include%20Indonesia%2C%20Iran%20and%20Senegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20countries%20have%20not%20specified%20how%20many%20deaths%20were%20heat-related.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaudi%20Health%20Minister%20Fahd%20bin%20Abdul%20Rahman%20Al-Jalajel%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20health%20plans%20for%20the%20hajj%20had%20%26quot%3Bbeen%20successfully%20carried%20out%26quot%3B%2C%20preventing%20major%20outbreaks%20of%20disease%20and%20other%20public%20health%20threats%2C%20the%20official%20Saudi%20Press%20Agency%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20officials%20%26quot%3Bprovided%20virtual%20consultations%20to%20over%205%2C800%20pilgrims%2C%20primarily%20for%20heat-related%20illnesses%2C%20enabling%20prompt%20intervention%20and%20mitigating%20the%20potential%20for%20a%20surge%20in%20cases%2C%26quot%3B%20SPA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718766600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-10%2Fv68nai_hajj-generic-istock_625x300_10_October_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fover-300-egyptian-pilgrims-die-in-hajj-most-from-heat-diplomats-5919901%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Diplomats%20on%20Tuesday%20said%20at%20least%20550%20pilgrims%20died%20during%20the%20hajj%2C%20underscoring%20the%20gruelling%20nature%20of%20the%20pilgrimage%20which%20again%20unfolded%20in%20scorching%20temperatures%20thi