000%20as%20a%20short%20sale.%20When%20we%20decided%20to%20pay%20it%20off%2C%20we%20had%20about%20%2493%2C000%20we%20still%20owed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20mom%20of%20three%20and%20now%20full-time%20blogger%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthriftylittlemom.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThrifty%20Little%20Mom%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20full%20%2493%2C000%20mortgage%20balance%20in%20two%20years%2C%20using%20two%20strategies%20to%20help%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20They%20kept%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20their%20mortgage's%20amortization%20table%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mortgage's%20amortization%20table%20shows%20the%20full%20amount%20of%20interest%20and%20principal%20for%20each%20payment.%20While%20the%20earlier%20payments%20go%20largely%20towards%20interest%20(especially%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F30-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20the%20later%20payments%20go%20more%20towards%20the%20principal%20balance.%20And%20they%20can%20come%20in%20handy%20for%20mortgage%20payoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%20and%20her%20husband%20paid%20close%20attention%20to%20their%20amortization%20table%20while%20planning%20their%20payoff%20and%20say%20it%20became%20a%20large%20part%20of%20their%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20plugged%20in%20what%20additional%20principal%20payment%20we%20could%20make%20each%20month%2C%20and%20it%20calculated%20how%20long%20it%20would%20take%20for%20us%20to%20pay%20off%20our%20loan%20based%20on%20paying%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20got%20obsessed%20with%20seeing%20the%20numbers%20drop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20started%20contributing%20more%20to%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgage-calculator%5C%22%3Emortgage%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20month%2C%20adding%20an%20extra%20%241%2C260%20to%20their%20%24689%20monthly%20payment%20and%C2%A0later%20increasing%20it%20to%20%242%2C515%20per%20month.%20That%20helped%20to%20further%20drop%20the%20principal%20on%20their%20loan%2C%20putting%20more%20of%20each%20payment%20towards%20the%20principal%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20watching%20this%20table%2C%20they%20could%20see%20how%20their%20hard%20work%20was%20paying%20off%20and%20how%20much%20further%20they%20had%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20They%20lived%20simply%20and%20contributed%20whatever%20they%20could%2C%20whenever%20they%20could%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20larger%2C%20regular%20monthly%20payments%20described%20above%2C%20the%20Andersons%20put%20whatever%20extra%20money%20they%20could%20towards%20their%20mortgage%20for%20two%20years.%20The%20couple%20was%20only%20living%20on%20one%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20her%20husband's%20engineering%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20so%20they%20contributed%20where%20they%20could%20and%20budgeted%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20was%20super%20simple%20during%20our%20debt%20payoff.%20We%20didn't%20do%20big%20vacations.%20We%20didn't%20buy%20new%20cars%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20just%20worked%20hard%2C%20lived%20contently%2C%20and%20saved%20where%20we%20could.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20saving%20on%20the%20splurges%20and%20extra%20purchases%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20mortgage%20quicker.%20Anderson%20also%20changed%20to%20a%20cash-based%20budgeting%20system%20to%20keep%20track%20of%20how%20much%20extra%20they%20were%20able%20to%20save%20each%20month.%20When%20she%20had%20money%20left%20over%20from%20her%20grocery%20budget%2C%20for%20example%2C%20she'd%20send%20it%20straight%20to%20the%20mortgage.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20literally%20go%20to%20the%20bank%2C%20fill%20out%20the%20slip%2C%20and%20hand%20them%20%2430%2C%20%2450%2C%20or%20%24100%20at%20a%20time%2C%20and%20it%20all%20helped%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20family%20put%20extra%20money%20they%20received%20throughout%20the%20year%20towards%20their%20mortgage.%20%26quot%3BTax%20refunds%20and%20monetary%20family%20gifts%20all%20went%20to%20the%20payoff%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwheres-my-tax-refund%5C%22%3ETax%20refunds%3C%2Fa%3E%20amounted%20to%20several%20thousand%20dollars%20for%20the%20family%20of%20five%2C%20and%20the%20couple%20also%20received%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20in%20bonuses%20from%20the%20husband's%20salary%2C%20according%20to%20financial%20records%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20Gifts%20from%20family%20were%20small%2C%20between%20%2425%20and%20%2450%20for%20holidays%20and%20birthdays%2C%20Anderson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20based%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20the%20Andersons%20were%20able%20to%20pay%20for%20their%20next%20home%20in%20cash%20after%20selling%20their%20paid-off%20Georgia%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaying%20off%20the%20mortgage%20has%20helped%20to%20bring%20her%20family%20peace.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20paid%20cash%20for%20our%20second%20house%20using%20the%20money%20we%20got%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20the%20first%20house%20we%20paid%20off%2C%20the%20motivation%20was%20to%20know%20that%20I%20had%20a%20home%20for%20my%20kids%20that%20couldn't%20be%20taken%20away%20by%20a%20bank%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%2