mp%20(left)%20and%20Chinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping%20(right)%20during%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%202019.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c09dc943bb77284ba36de4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20(left)%20and%20Chinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping%20(right)%20during%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%202019.%20Trump%20had%20been%20in%20office%20from%202017%20to%202020.%3Cp%3EBrendan%20Smialowski%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWolfsthal%20said%20that%20if%20the%20US%20resumed%20testing%2C%20it%20%26quot%3Bwould%20only%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20RF%20%5BRussian%20Federation%5D%20and%20PRC%20%5BPeople's%20Republic%20of%20China%5D%20to%20resume%20nuclear%20testing%20and%20catch%20up.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20new%20nuclear%20materials%20also%20weren't%20needed%2C%20as%20the%20US%20has%20stockpiles%20available%20from%20the%20Cold%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNuclear%20bullying%20doesn't%20work%20and%20leads%20to%20arms%20racing%2C%26quot%3B%20Daryl%20Kimball%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Arms%20Control%20Association%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FDarylGKimball%2Fstatus%2F1803055596066738325%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20calling%20O'Brien's%20opinion%20%26quot%3Bdangerous%2C%20counterproductive%20Dr.%20Strangelove%20thinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20wins%20a%20nuclear%20arms%20race%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKimball%20called%20out%20the%20difference%20between%20O'Brien's%20argument%20for%20the%20resumption%20of%20nuclear%20testing%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20current%20policy%2C%20which%20remains%20dedicated%20to%20the%20status%20quo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20United%20States%20does%20not%20need%20to%20increase%20our%20nuclear%20forces%20to%20outnumber%20the%20combined%20total%20of%20our%20competitors%20in%20order%20to%20successfully%20deter%20them.%20We've%20been%20there.%20We've%20learned%20that%20lesson%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20truly%20effective%20nuclear%20deterrence%20comes%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bbetter%26quot%3B%20approach%2C%20not%20a%20%26quot%3Bmore%26quot%3B%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20repeatedly%20detonated%20nuclear%20weapons%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20most%20often%20at%20the%20remote%20Nevada%20Test%20Site%2C%20where%20the%20explosions%20could%20be%20seen%20in%20Las%20Vegas.%20The%20nuclear%20surface%20explosions%20shifted%20deep%20underground%20in%201962%20and%20continued%20until%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22russia%20nuclear%20weapons%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a1b33ae7101ad75ba442f7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221136%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShell%2C%20which%20is%20the%20replica%20of%20the%20biggest%20detonated%20Soviet%20nuclear%20bomb%20AN-602%20(Tsar-Bomb)%2C%20on%20display%20in%20Moscow%2C%20Russia.%3Cp%3EMaxim%20Zmeyev%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Lewis%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Middlebury%20Institute%20of%20International%20Studies%20at%20Monterey%20and%20a%20nuclear%20proliferation%20expert%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FArmsControlWonk%2Fstatus%2F1803059575991505226%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20thread%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20number%20of%20US%20nuke%20tests%20%E2%80%94%201%2C149%20%E2%80%94%20is%20more%20than%20that%20of%20Russia%2C%20969%2C%20and%20China%2C%2045%2C%20combined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BResuming%20nuclear%20testing%20would%20reduce%20US%20technical%20superiority%20over%20Russia%20and%20China%20because%20they%20would%20immediately%20follow%20and%20have%20much%20more%20to%20learn%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20been%20expanding%20its%20arsenal%2C%20stockpiling%20more%20than%20500%20operational%20nuclear%20warheads%20as%20of%20May%202023%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20said%20last%20fall%20in%20its%20annual%20China%20Military%20Power%20Report.%20But%20even%20if%20that%20doubles%20to%201%2C000%20by%202030%2C%20as%20the%20Pentagon%20estimates%2C%20it'll%20still%20pale%20in%20comparison%20to%20the%20US%20and%20Russia's%20numbers%3A%205%2C044%20and%205%2C580%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20Foreign%20Affairs%20story%2C%20O'Brien%20suggests%20that%20increased%20US%20development%20and%20testing%20will%20help%20deter%20China%2C%20rather%20than%20compel%20it%20to%20counter%20the%20growing%20US%20capabilities%20in%20an%20arms%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHans%20Kristensen%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Nuclear%20Information%20Project%20at%20the%20Federation%20of%20American%20Scientists%2C%20said%20in%20a%20social%20media%20post%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20are%20some%20'advisors'%20you%20just%20shouldn't%20take%20advice%20from.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Brien's%20push%20for%20resumed%20testing%20shouldn't%20necessarily%20come%20as%20a%20surprise.%20Back%20in%20June%202020%2C%20in%20the%20final%20months%20of%20Trump's%20presidency%2C%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20told%20Congress%20it%20suspected%20Russia%20and%20China%20had%20defied%20testing%20moratoriums%2C%20raising%20concerns%20the%20US%20would%20follow.%20Just%20a%20month%20prior%2C%20US%20officials%20considered%20conducting%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Brapid%20test%26quot%3B%20just%20to%20demonstrate%20readiness%20to%20America's%20adversaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20experts%20pushed%20back%20on%20both%20the%20State%20Department's%20accusations%20and%20the%20potential%20for%20resumed%20testing%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20US%20does%20many%20of%20the%20same%20activities%20as%20Russia%20and%20China%20without%20conducting%20full%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20remained%20unclear%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Funited-states%2F2020%2F06%2F24%2Fwill-donald-trump-resume-nuclear-testing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eif%20Trump%20would%20have%20been%20game%20for%20resumed%20nuclear%20testing%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20breaking%20the%20longstanding%20Comprehensive%20Test%20Ban%20Treaty%2C%20but%20his%20first-term%20advisors%2C%20such%20as%20O'Brien's%20predecessor%20John%20Bolton%2C%20believed%20%26quot%3Bunsigning%26quot%3B%20the%20treaty%20should%20be%20a%20top%20priority%20for%20the%20US.%20Now%2C%20the%20discussion%20is%20back%20again.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-trump-official-wants-restart-us-nuke-testing-experts-disagree-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718741685000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6671d20f087acd2be9b4af84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-trump-official-wants-restart-us-nuke-testing-experts-disagree-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Robert%20O'Brien's%20call%20to%20restart%20nuclear%20weapons%20testing%20was%20met%20with%20resounding%20criticism%20from%20experts%2C%20who%20called%20it%20ignorant%20and%20dangerous.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A63%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-trump-official-wants-restart-us-nuke-testing-experts-disagree-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%2010%20best%20lip%20balms%20with%20SPF%20that%20prevent%20chapped%2C%20burned%20lips%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.co