er%2C%20queer)%20community%20in%20India.%20The%20young%20boy%20had%20no%20one%20to%20turn%20to%20understand%20how%20he%20felt%20and%20share%20his%20feelings%20with.%20The%20absence%20of%20someone%20who%20was%20openly%20gay%20cost%20Srivatsan%20a%20lot%20of%20pain%20in%20his%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20Srivatsan%20shared%20his%20sexuality%20with%20someone%2C%20all%20hell%20broke%20loose.%20Turns%20out%20that%20the%20person%20he%20shared%20it%20with%20was%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20friend%20who%20violated%20Srivatsan%E2%80%99s%20trust%20by%20blurting%20out%20the%20information%20to%20his%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20is%20a%20priest%20and%20tried%20to%20do%20conversion%20therapy%20on%20me.%20They%20sent%20me%20to%20an%20uncle%E2%80%99s%20place%20and%20made%20me%20do%20some%20religious%20activities%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20I%20would%20%E2%80%98change%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20a%20very%20low%20point%20in%20my%20life.%20I%20was%20denied%20everything%20I%20liked%2C%20even%20books%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Srivatsan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20parents%20refused%20to%20talk%20to%20him%20and%20were%20%E2%80%9Cashamed%E2%80%9D%20of%20what%20he%20had%20become%2C%20he%20adds.%20The%20only%20way%20out%2C%20they%20told%20him%2C%20was%20to%20marry%20a%20girl.%20To%20gain%20his%20parents%E2%80%99%20acceptance%20and%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20son%E2%80%9D%2C%20Srivatsan%20even%20tried%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20wanted%20my%20parents%20to%20accept%20me.%20I%20went%20the%20whole%20nine%20yards%20and%20even%20saw%20a%20girl%20my%20parents%20had%20chosen.%20They%20felt%20that%20once%20I%20got%20married%20to%20a%20girl%2C%20everything%20would%20be%20okay%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20the%20digital%20solutions%20consultant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20even%20though%20he%20wanted%20to%20make%20his%20parents%20happy%2C%20he%20realised%20that%20it%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20done%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20his%20own%20happiness.%20He%20was%20torn%20betw